rComments: Probably the best professor I've had through my entire first year. All Health Sci and Nursing students should look for him and Carnegie. He explains material clearly and his evals are very straightforward. He makes good demonstrations and has his dog on his lap during lectures. Clearly passionate about teaching

Really good prof that definitely saved me during the second half of anatomy. Definitely would recommend being in his section if you want to succeed as long as you get through the first half. Wish he taught more anatomy classes lmao.
Great prof. Really appreciated the review questions he would do at the end of lectures, and a decent amount of them would show up on evals. Thorough, clear, accessible, fair.
Amazing professor, lectures aren't very long and he explains everything very well. Exams and midterms are very fair and you'll do well as long as you study. Definitely take Professor Downey.

Super great prof! Answers emails very fast and goes long ways to ensure you understand the content. His exams are fair game and if you show up and study youll do great! ANP classes are heavy so be prepared for a big workload but downey makes it not too bad and his lectures are not extremely long! TAKE HIS CLASS

Dr. Downey saved ANP1105. His lectures were clear, and made learning ANP a breeze. His review sessions were super helpful. His section on the exam was easy, not only because he taught us well, but also because his MCQ weren't double layer trick questions. Super accessible, he even hosted an AMA before the semester. Knows what he's talking about.

Really recommend Dr. Downey! His lectures are straight-forward and are easy to understand. He is very organized and is always available to answer questions. His midterm questions are very true to the material in his lectures. You can tell he really wants his students to succeed!

Format of lectures were youtube vids so it was easy to pause and go back whenever needed. Vids were the slideshows and his face on the side explaining which I found more engaging than the voice overs other profs did. Made sure you understood material and would repeat important info. Had practice questions at end of lecs. Tests were multiple choice

Dr. Downey was a good prof. He made sure that we understood his material and he always responded to emails. He gives clear explanations. He also gives practice questions for his midterms. You kinda do have to read the textbook though. But his midterm question are fair enough. Make sure to keep up with the recorded videos. He is an average professor

I recommend Downey if you can. He carried and actually taught compared to my other prof paired with him. His Youtube lectures are roughly 50-60 minutes long each, but they're in depth. He puts review questions at the end that sometimes end up on the exams. He makes it easy to understand the processes. Overall, good prof.
AWESOME. freaking cool d00d. <3

Dr. Downey is a real gem. He is so passionate about what he teaches and you can EASILY understand his material. ANP is not an easy course, but if you attend his lectures/watch his videos you should be just fine!

he is an amazing professor. i will be choosing my future physio classes around what he teaches. very clear lectures. if you watch all his lectures, he teaches so well that you don't have to study bc you'll learn it perfectly in the first place. he's a real gem

Downey is an angel on earth. He truly cares about his students and does all that he can to accommodate them. His lectures were clear and engaging, and his midterms were fair. He also posts practice multiple choice questions, which were incredibly helpful when preparing for the midterms and finals. Overall, great prof. I really enjoyed his class.

Great prof! Really enjoyed his half of ANP1105. He went into a lot of detail during the lectures and used really good examples, and made sure to keep us intrigued. Also posted practice questions after each unit to prepare us for the exam, and held many review sessions. I would recommend taking his class!

So grateful that Dr. Downey took over for Dr. Gee, he is so caring and really wants his students to succeed. Good lectures and provides practice questions at the end that sometimes show up on the midterm.
He is a gift to Gee students.

Dr. Downey is literally THE most perfect lecturer, and actually seems like he does want his students to do well. Best combo! Super kind in emails, not rude at all. First year students, definitely take his ANP 1105 class if you get the chance!!!!

Dr. Downey is a really nice professor who seemingly cares about his students and their understanding of the course. Easy to ask questions to and an overall nice guy. Teaches ANP well and knows his stuff :)
This man is my KING. One point on my anatomy final stood between me and a scholarship, and he helped me get the grade I needed. He's one of those profs that really cares about his students' success.
Dr Downey is a great prof. His lectures are very engaging and he is a pretty cool guy too!
Not my favourite prof but still pretty good. I find it better to just read the textbook. Gives a ton of sample questions at the end of each lecture which can help with your understanding.

The slides were awesome, set up in a way that really helps you learn. Prof explains the content well in lectures, but reading the textbook is the best way to understand the material. He's a nice guy and his exams were more than fair. Solid anatomy prof.

Overall a solid proff . Was always available outside of class for extra help and often does review multiple choice questions/answers which sometimes end up on the exam. exams are very detailed and are multiple choice so study hard!

Really nice guy who is always happy to answer questions. Responds to emails very quickly and is very accommodating. Didn't go to all of the lectures because his slides are detailed and he has good footnotes, and the textbook is an excellent source.

You can tell that Dr. Downey puts a lot of effort into making his slides easy to read and full of important info. He runs study groups before each exam and is really approachable and more than willing to answer questions. Would recommend using the textbook to study for midterms and final.

Spectacular prof, uses footnotes to try and simplify heavy content lectures. Exam are hard mainly because this course has so much information although he does his best to make it as simple as possible. Lectures are posted online although going to class may be helpful as he elaborates on certain concepts in class.
I really enjoy this prof! Very caring and has excellent review sessions before the midterms and exams! Overall a great guy and a great professor!
